\begin_layout Standard
Now returning to our objective of framing a our decision, we must translate
 each of the bbas in Tables 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Conditional BBAs"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Prior bbas on S"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 into Pignistic Transforms using (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: Pignistic Xform"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
 These appear in Tables 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Pignistic-bba xforms on H"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Pignistic-bba transforms on S"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 These are the Bayesian probabilities derived from our ToE representation
 for application to the decision tree.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The probabilities on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{H}$
\end_inset

 in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Pignistic-bba xforms on H"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 for the distinct structural states 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \text{None}\right\} $
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \text{Open}\right\} $
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \text{Closed}\right\} $
\end_inset

 serve the same purpose as the conditional probabilities from Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Bayesian Oil-Field Conditionals"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 do in the Bayesian framing.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $Bet_{P^{\mathcal{H}}}\big[m^{\mathcal{S}}\big]\left(s\right)$
\end_inset

 functions like the marginal 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}\left(S\right)$
\end_inset

.
 And the 
\begin_inset Formula $Bet_{P^{\mathcal{S}}}\left(s\right)$
\end_inset

 quantities from Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Pignistic-bba transforms on S"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 are equivalent to the Bayesian marginals 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}\left(h\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

