\begin_layout Standard
What is occurring here? The ToE yields much-lower degrees of certainty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An exercise in KL-distance calculation allows for exploration of this hypothesis.
 We seek to compare the Bayesian-probability structure of 
\begin_inset Formula $Bet_{P^{\mathscr{H}}}\left[s\right]\left(h\right)$
\end_inset

 with that for 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}\left(h,x\right)$
\end_inset

 in our Bayesian decision framing.
 Our 
\begin_inset Formula $Bet_{P^{\mathscr{H}}}\left[s\right]\left(h\right)$
\end_inset

 quantities from Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Pignistic-bba xforms on H"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 are effectively conditional probabilities conditioned on 
\begin_inset Formula $Bet_{P^{\mathcal{S}}}\left(s\right)$
\end_inset

 from Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Pignistic-bba transforms on S"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 Converting 
\begin_inset Formula $Bet_{P^{\mathscr{H}}}\left[s\right]\left(h\right)$
\end_inset

 gives us 
\begin_inset Formula $Bet_{P^{\mathscr{H}\times\mathcal{S}}}\left(h,s\right)$
\end_inset

.
 This 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

joint
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 distribution is on a compatible frame of discernment with that for 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}\left(h,x\right)$
\end_inset

 .
\end_layout

